    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, BUMPER AND RUNNING BOARDS - MXT - ADJUSTMENTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ADJUSTMENTS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="2">
            <title>HOOD ADJUSTMENT AND ALIGNMENT</title>
            <para>The MXT hood can be adjusted by moving the hinge plate attachment located at the front cross member.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust the hood left to right</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen the hinge attachment bolts and slide the hinge plate assembly left or
                        right.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check the alignment with the hood contour lines. If the hood alignment is proper,
                        tighten the hinge plate bolts. Torque to required value.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To adjust hood forward and back (reference Figure 49), loosen the hinge mounting bolts
                    at the mounting plate (Item 1) on the chassis front cross member (Item 2).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Slide the hood forward or aft as required.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Check the distance between the rear edge of hood and clearance to windshield.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Verify that the two front snubbers (Item 1, Figure 50) are impacting on the mega
                        brackets (Item 2, Figure 50) when hood is closed.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten the hinge mounting bolts and torque to required values.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
